      "content": "i've been looking at the packet headers and metadata for high-frequency institutional transfers lately... there's this weird residue, like certain hex values aren't actually part of the protocol but are being used to carry value. it’s almost like the actual cash is just a placeholder and the real wealth is being moved through the metadata itself. does that even make sense from a tech standpoint?",
